result.name: Royal Park Hotel

reviews.text: Very conveniently located. Rooms are spacious by Hong Kong standards. Nice leisure pool. Wish there were proper wine glasses and also better TV / movie selections.

in the centre of Sha Tin.  Next to the main shopping centre, a river and a park.  Can walk in the park for leisure and along the river.  The HK Heritage Museum is in the nearby.  Everything is good for a tourist.  Highly recommended!

We've found the Royal Park Hotel to be perfect for our needs. Conjoint to the Shatin shopping complex we've had no trouble getting around or meeting with friends. Rooms are spacious enough for a toddler to run around in and are well insulated.

I've been staying at the Royal Park Hotel for over 10 years on the past 5 visits to Hong Kong for the convenience of its location, but my recent visit has been by far the worst stay.We were woken up at 7am and 2am on 2 separate occasions by a faulty fire alarm. My parents who are both over 60 years old, both with mobility issues, frantically ran down 7 flights of stairs to make our way out the building only to be told twice that it was a false alarm (stayed during 26th to 29th June and then 3rd to 6th July). This is followed by an apology and a generic excuse about the alarm being triggered by condensation coming from a shower and that it was very "normal" for this to happen. The staff's attitude has been very dismissive and the other guests affected had not been offered any further compensation for the disruption (some ran out the fire exits in their bare foot and their night gowns).The room I stayed in (room 1321) also had a leaky air conditioning system. I almost slipped during the night when I walked to the toilet, stepping into a pool of water.If you want a good night sleep, then I would not recommend you to stay at the Royal Park Hotel due to my recent experience. For over HK$1000 a night, you can find more attentive service and a good night sleep elsewhere.
Hotel is nice, connected to a large shopping mall. Kinda far from Hong Kong.

reviews.text: check in 櫃檯非常天兵，也不問清楚就擅自把我女友放到我同學的房。

在餐廳方面，於2006年曾經進行改革及翻新工程。位於酒店大堂的「花月軒」（大堂酒廊）被One+One Bar取代。酒店三樓西式餐廳「百勝閣」被2+2 Café取代。只有櫻田日本餐廳及帝都糕餅店仍保留至今。

帝都酒店擁有448間客房，房間面積約為300平方呎。當中有436間客房及12間套房，並提供服務式住宅及酒店住宿服務。為配合2008年北京奧運馬術項目於沙田舉行，新鴻基地產耗資三億元為客房及酒店進行翻新工程，工程包括提升酒店大堂、客房、餐廳、泳池和健身室等設施，並加強保安、電腦及電話系統。在保安方面，升降機採用全新的多功能智能咭系統及數碼監察系統，保障賓客的隱私，防止閒人進入客房樓層。此外，為殘奧期間作好準備，特設輪椅人士而設的房間。

在食肆方面，西式餐廳包括酒店地下的One+One Bar及三樓的2+2 Café，提供歐陸及亞洲多種各式美食。中式餐廳為酒店二樓的帝都軒及潮都軒，供應粵菜及潮州菜。位於三樓開業十多年的「櫻田日本餐廳」於2006年進行翻新後，提供不少新派日本菜。餐廳更採用開放式設計，讓食客欣賞鐵板燒烹調情況。為接待奧運馬術選手，位於酒店地下的海鮮酒家於2007年12月結業後，耗資4000萬元裝修更換為全新的華麗中菜廳，命名為「帝玉庭」，於2008年6月19日開業。2008年9月帝都軒結業，原址裝修更換為時尚富麗的餐廳扒房，命名為City Art Restaurant，於2008年12月30日開業。餐廳設有開放式火山石烤爐廚房、貴賓房及一間較大型的貴賓用餐區。

連接新城市商業大廈天橋位置設有帝都糕餅店，提供多種甜品、麵包及各款特色西餅蛋糕。
杖婆婆媽媽活在自己的生活圈的人都有一個人都有一個頭兩年前面班機起來了
Very conveniently located. Rooms are spacious by Hong Kong standards. Nice leisure pool. Wish there were proper wine glasses and also better TV / movie selections.
